In [3]:
category_counts = df['County'].value_counts()


heatmap_data = pd.DataFrame(category_counts).reset_index()
heatmap_data.columns = ['County', '# of Times']


plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
heatmap = sns.heatmap(heatmap_data.pivot_table(index='County', aggfunc='sum'), cmap="Reds", annot=True, fmt="d")
heatmap.set_title('Heatmap of Category Counts')
heatmap.set_ylabel('County')


plt.show()

plt.title('Distribution of Organizations by County')
plt.axis('equal') 
plt.show()

plt.title('Distribution of Organizations by County')
plt.axis('equal')
plt.show()

In [8]:
school_type_counts = df2['School Type'].value_counts()

# Create a bar chart
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
school_type_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='skyblue')
plt.title('Distribution of School Types - 2023')
plt.xlabel('School Type')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)
plt.show()

# Create a pie chart
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
school_type_counts.plot(kind='pie', autopct='%1.1f%%', colors=['lightcoral', 'lightgreen', 'lightskyblue'], startangle=140)
plt.title('Distribution of School Types - 2023')
plt.ylabel('')  # Remove the y-label
plt.axis('equal')  # Equal aspect ratio ensures that pie is drawn as a circle
plt.show()
